

!!! run docker-compose.yml file (zookeeper and kafka services) in a terminal:
    cd services/order-service
    docker-compose up -d

    stop kafka:
    docker-compose down

    Checking topics in the Kafka:
        1. Go to Docker Desktop -> open Kafka server
        2. In the Kafka terminal input:
            check topics:
                kafka-topics --list --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
            reading message from topic (here we will see orderIds):
                kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic order-created-topic --from-beginning



Checking by Postman:

1. create new order
    POST    http://localhost:8083/api/v1/orders/create

    Headers:
        Content-Type: application/json

    Body -> raw:
        {
          "userId": "1",
          "productId": "68090e121e240f0ca003c49d",
          "quantity": 2,
          "totalPrice": 2400.0
        }

    We get data about order:
        {
            "id": 1,
            "userId": "1",
            "productId": "68090e121e240f0ca003c49d",
            "quantity": 2,
            "totalPrice": 2400.0
        }